Author: CoinSeason
Title: [ANN][PreICO] CoinSeason - Canada's Fast Growing Digital Exchange Platform
Body: CoinSeason is a subsidiary of Volctech Blockchain Inc.(founded by William Wang, Jack Wang and James Li, who are also the Founders of CoinSeason). CoinSeason is an unique technology innovation company in Vancouver growing at a remarkable speed. The Articles of Association and the Anti-Money Laundering and Anti-Terrorist Financing Policy and Procedure of CoinSeason Capital Inc. are handled by a professional legal team and are fully governed by the Financial Transactions and Reports Analysis Centre of Canada (FINTRAC).     Since 2017, the governments of countries such as Russia, Japan, Singapore, Israel, Sweden, Dubai, and Estonia have stated that they would consider issuing statutory digital currencies. With the booming development of blockchain industry, the attitude of countries towards digital assets has gradually developed from prohibition to recognition and implementation and has gradually begun to manage and regulate the market, which marks the future trend of blockchain assets. Digital assets, blockchain and other technologies are the technological innovation that the current financial industry craves. In Canada, the digital encrypted currency market has gradually become more standardized, and regulators are very positive about ICO. On August 27, 2017, the Canadian Securities Administration issued a statement saying that the ICO token was may be a security and required to comply with the Canadian Securities Act. Meanwhile, companies that are about to issue ICOs were welcome to enter the ‚ÄúRegulatory Sandbox‚Äù to test new financial products in a limited environment. On January 31, 2018, the Canadian government announced cooperation with the World Economic Forum and the Dutch government to launch a blockchain identification system. At the same time, Bill Morneau, Minister of Finance of Canada indicated that Canada would not change its current tax code for Bitcoin. CoinSeason trading platform is located in such a country with a friendly policy, adhering to professionalism and integrity to open up a safe, stable and legal trading platform for customers.  With the fast growing blockchain industry and cryptocurrency market, CoinSeason understands how much the digital asset holders want to have a secure, stable, and credible platform with competitive fees.  With the blockchain industry booming around the world, CoinSeason aims to provide a fast and secure investment platform for the public. CoinSeason provides output ports for blockchain technology, in order to promote the development and application of blockchain technology.    The CoinSeason team believes that blockchain and cryptocurrency are the revolutionary tools to unleash the potential in all business sectors.  Our team is excited to witness the power of blockchain and come join us by participating our ICO! Core Team William Wang James Li Jack Wang Founder and CEO of CoinSeason Co-founder and CTO of CoinSeason Co-founder and COO of CoinSeason --- --- --- Dan Song Nicki Yang Xinyi Wang CFO of CoinSeason Director of Fund Management of CoinSeason Chief Architect of CoinSeason --- --- --- Fei Yan Frank Zhang Eric Li Chief R & D Engineer of CoinSeason Chief Big Data Analyst of CoinSeason Sales Director of CoinSeason --- --- --- Erica Wang Clover Zhou Product Director of CoinSeason Marketing Director of CoinSeason --- ---     The CoinSeason platform will be fully up and running in June 2018. The upcoming CoinSeason token (CSZ) will be issued in September 2018 and token owners can use CSZ as utility token to reduce trading commission cost. Once the CoinSeason trading platform is fully up and running, CoinSeason will serve the market with competitive fees and services.  CoinSeason is currently in the process of applying for ‚Äúmarketplace‚Äù status, which simply means the company will be licensed to trade securities and related product, allowing CoinSeason to expand the business. More Details we be available in the near future!   [ Website | Telegram | Facebook | Twitter | Medium | LinkedIn | GitHub ]
